features: Modeled After Breast Milk & made with carefully sourced premium ingredients, this formula is made with organic lactose the principal carbohydrate found in breast milk. Our formula provides key vitamins and minerals that are found naturally in breast milk.

With 4X More Prebiotics than most other organic infant formula, our formula delivers two prebiotics, GOS & FOS, Fibers that mimic the function of prebiotics found naturally in breast milk, which promote healthy gut bacteria in infants. No corn syrup. State of Readiness: Ready to Eat

Happy Baby: At Happy Baby Organics, we provide organic and delicious options for your baby's nutritional journey. We develop premium organic recipes perfectly matched with your child's age and stage. This is enlightened nutrition for every family.

Mindfully Made: We develop premium organic recipes perfectly matched with your child's age and stage. Explore our snacks & meals for growing babies, toddlers & kids, from baby food pouches to freeze-dried yogurt treats, organic Cereals & Toddler Snacks.
Happy Baby: For happy tummies and Happy Tots, try Happy Baby's full line of baby food pouches, organic Cereals, teething wafers & baby snacks and more
body.description: Modeled after breast milk, our Stage 2 organic infant formula is crafted with carefully sourced, premium ingredients, and tailored to meet the nutritional needs of babies six months of age or older. Happy Baby Organic Infant Formula thoughtfully combines organic lactose, dual prebiotics, and essential nutrients, including calcium, vitamin D, iron, DHA, ARA, folic acid, and choline, to help nourish and support your little one during this precious time of development. Here's to a happy start! Before using an infant formula, ask the advice of your healthcare professional. Powdered infant formulas are not sterile and should not be fed to premature infants or infants who might have immune problems unless directed and supervised by your baby's doctor.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Previous page Complete nutrition with Lactose Lactose is the #1 component in breast milk, which is why it's #1 in our formula, too. Complete nutrition with Expert-recommended DHA Also found in breast milk, we include DHA to help support brain and eye development. Complete nutrition with Our GOS & FOS Helps promote softer stools, closer to breastfed infants’**. Next page 1 Lactose 2 Expert-recommended DHA 3 Dual Prebiotics

What’s the Difference Between Our Formulas? Stage 1: 0–12 months Stage 1 Sensitive: 0–12 months Stage 2: 6–12 months At-a-glance: Specially formulated to provide complete nutrition for the first year of life At-a-glance: Reduced lactose for sensitive bellies; complete nutrition for baby’s first year At-a-glance: Tailored to little ones’ development starting at 6 months Key ingredients: Made with organic lactose, prebiotics, and key vitamins & minerals. Key ingredients: Made with 75% reduced lactose for babies experiencing fussiness & gas. Key ingredients: Higher levels of key nutrients including calcium, choline, and iron.

Happy Baby Infant Formula Mixing Instructions Step 1 Wash hands and surfaces. Pour desired amount of warm water (approximately 100°F/40°C) into a clean bottle. Step 2 Add powder to water in bottle. (See Feeding Chart on back of canister.) Step 3 Cap bottle and shake well until powder is dissolved. Step 4 Feed immediately and discard used formula within 1 hour.

How many bottles can I make from one 21oz tub? You can prepare around 18–19 8-oz bottles with our 21oz tubs. How long does Happy Baby formula last? Please refer to the Use By date on the bottom of each formula tub. Once the tub has been opened, formula can be used for one month. We do not recommend using the formula after 30 days of opening. Can I prepare a bottle and store in the refrigerator? Yes, you can prepare formula in advance. Make sure to store prepared formula in the refrigerator and use it within 24 hours. Do not store any leftover formula that you have already fed to baby. What’s the best water temperature for mixing? We suggest preparing our formula with warm water (approximately 100F, or 40C). This temperature, which is just above body temp, will help to dissolve the formula properly. If the water is too cool, it will not mix properly.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 19, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My son did great on it.
reviews.reviewText: At first when I realized I was going to have problems breastfeeding for a second time, this time with a diagnosis of IGT, I started with HiPP formula. My son did great on it. It's a great product. But it's not legally sold in the US, so I had to go through 3rd party sites. That.... Made me feel a bit uneasy. But every time I tried something different for my son, he got wicked constipated. Every mommy hates, watching her tiny baby struggle to pass poops.Then I tried Pure Bliss by Similac. It's made with grass fed milk. That one he did well on as well. But it's $35 a can. About the same as HiPP.FINALLY, I tried this. More affordable and he took well to it, no digestive issues.This is the one we have stuck with for the last 5 months. I think this'll be our last order--we buy this 3 boxes at a time and it lasts about 6 weeks. By then he'll be very close to 1 years old and we can transition away from formula. Yay!!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 5, 2019
reviews.reviewText: My baby loves this formula. He has been exclusively breastfed but am starting to wean him a bit. I originally tried Enfamil but he absolutely hated it and refused to eat. I found this formula and really loved that it is non-GMO and organic. I especially loved that the first ingredient is lactose and not corn syrup solids like most formulas. My baby drinks with formula with no problem and it seems to be working well for him-no gas or fussiness. As far as the price I don't think it's that bad. Enfamil charges a few bucks more for 20 oz tub. Of course there are store brand formulas like Walmart for cheap but one would call into question the quality. For an organic and non-GMO formula the price is right.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 10, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great product and no stomach issues!
reviews.reviewText: We really like this formula. It does have bubbles like others say, but if you stir with a spoon, or swirl it fast in the bottle without shaking it, it only has a few bubbles.My son is 12 months old and has been breastfeeding since. We are using this to wean and he has had zero issues. We bought another brand prior to this and did not have this good of a result. I feel less guilty weaning when I have a good product to supplement.This is an honest review from an Amazon customer. Let me know if you found this helpful.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 2, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great alternative to Holle
reviews.reviewText: I have been using Holle organic formula ever since having to supplement for my baby and the latest purchase i made was wholesale, from Germany, so it didn't get here before i almost ran out. That is how i ended up purchasing this formula and my baby loves it! It's so nice that American formulas are concentrated (1 scoop per 2oz) vs the bulky European ones (1 scoop per 1oz). Makes it a lot less measuring and counting when making a bottle. No problems with taste or her rejecting it or anything like that. No increase in gas or stomach issues or anything either. Overall, I'd use this again, and maybe from the getgo with next baby!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 5, 2017
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love this formula for our dairy & coconut allergy baby!
reviews.reviewText: I know what your thinking... this is a dairy formula and our baby has a dairy allergy so why would you give him this... I’m not sure if the cows being grass fed has anything to do with it but this formula works for our baby without any discomfort, colic or constipation. It rivals Hipp Organic (which I am a big fan of) without the wait time for arrival and can be found locally without any problems. If your child has any allergies, please give the formula a try and see if it makes them better before using any of the toxic, foul smelling alimentum and other formulas doctors may recommend. I’ll also add I love that it makes the baby poops yellow line breastmilk with no bad/foul smell 😊
